name: Urn
summary:
Finnish old school black/thrash metal, founded by former Barathrum-members, although as of 2008, only Sulphur remains in the band.

Current line-up
Sulphur - Vocals, Guitar, Bass (ex-Barathrum)


Discography

Promo 1997 Demo 1997
Rehearsal tape Demo 1997
I Am Your Nightmare EP 1999
Studio rehearsal Demo 2000
666 Megatons Full-length 2001
The Nameless Wraith / Morbid Death Split 2004
Promo 2005 Demo, 2005
Dawn Of The Devastation Full-length 2006

name: Pailhead
summary: Pailhead is a collaboration between Ian MacKaye (Minor Threat, Teen Idles, Fugazi, Embrace, etc.) and Ministry. The combo debuted in 1987 with the "I Will Refuse"/"No Bunny" 7", and followed that with the Trait EP in 1988.  (The Trait CD included both releases.)  The music is fairly typical of Ministry circa The Land of Rape and Honey, over which MacKaye shouts his politically-inclined lyrics.
